<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>The example shows excellent what's wrong:</p>

<p>for( $i=1990; $i&lt;2010; $i++ ){
      $oDate = new Zend_Date( $i . '-01-1' );
      echo $oDate-&gt;toString("YYYY-MM-dd") . '<br />';
}</p>

<p>outputs:</p>

<p>31-12-1991 should be 1990-12-31
31-12-1992 should be 1991-12-31
31-12-1992 should be 1992-12-31
31-12-1993 should be 1993-12-31
31-12-1994 should be 1994-12-31
31-12-1995 should be 1995-12-31
31-12-1997 should be 1996-12-31
31-12-1998 should be 1997-12-31
31-12-1998 should be 1998-12-31
31-12-1999 should be 1999-12-31
31-12-2000 should be 2000-12-31
31-12-2002 should be 2001-12-31
31-12-2003 should be 2002-12-31
31-12-2004 should be 2003-12-31
31-12-2004 should be 2004-12-31
31-12-2005 should be 2005-12-31
31-12-2006 should be 2006-12-31
31-12-2008 should be 2007-12-31
31-12-2009 should be 2008-12-31
31-12-2009 should be 2009-12-31</p>

<p>This is not only for the 31th of December, but it shows nicely what goes wrong.</p>

<p>However the y-MM-dd format produces the right output.</p>

